re lighter and yellowish. Emeralds from Zimbabwe are smaller is size and lighter in shade. However the term \'African emerald\' is a misnomer. It simply denotes green fluorite.\n\nThis Gem of Lord Ganesha is the favoured Gem of the people seeking intellectual powers as well as for those seeking wealth .This calms down the nervous system and improves the capacity to take decisions. It improves the liquidity and money flow in business and blesses the wearer with liquid assets.\n\nEmeralds are also cut in many other, mainly classical shapes, but if the raw material contains a large number of inclusions, it may often be cut into a gently rounded cabochon, or into one of the emerald beads which are so popular in India.\n\nSo how can you protect yourself from these \'fakes\'? best way is to buy from a specialist in whom you have confidence. Emerald should only be purchased with a report from a reputable gemological institute. You can differentiate reliably between natural and synthetic emeralds."]
    
